SIMPLE: prisoner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prisoner
<hw>Pris"on*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>prisonnier</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is confined in a
prison.</def> <rj><au>Piers Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person under arrest, or in custody, whether in
prison or not; a person held in involuntary restraint; a captive;
<as>as, a <ex>prisoner</ex> at the bar of a court</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Prisoner</qex> of Hope thou art, -- look up and sing.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Prisoner's base</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Base</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 24.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prisonment</ent>⟦br⟧
